description:
In this episode, we learn about the Morning Star. The Southern States of the United States of America were a relatively unentered field when the Morning Star boat set sail from Michigan, to arrive in the south. This boat acted as a schoolhouse, meeting room, and library amongst other things, during a time that these locations would often get torched. This was a genius idea and gave great impetus to the gospel work.

To find out more about the Morning Star boat visit our website to read our extended article.
